name: **Rabbit Island**
description: Rabbit Island M327-242 Sheet 46 Understudy to the nearby Hare Island (the pair are called the Leverets), Rabbit is cut off from the mainland at all points of the tide. It is a small low-lying overgrown unattractive lump, given over to cormorant, Sea Radish, and nettles. It commands quite a large footprint at LW. Land on the W side of the NE tip onto stones as the rest of the shore is boulders.
